  "322": {
    "inputs": {
      "value": "DURATION:\n4 seconds\n\nFORMAT:\nVertical 9:16 cinematic video, 24 fps, shallow depth of field, analog film texture.\n\nSTYLE:\nRetro-futurist 1970s broadcast horror, practical effects, dim CRT glow, soft lens diffusion, subtle VHS noise, eerie but grounded.\n\nSCENE:\nA tired broadcast technician sits alone in a dark control room filled with old CRT monitors, switches, cables, and a glowing red ON AIR sign.\n\nCAMERA:\nSlow push-in from the side of his face toward the nearest CRT monitor. No cuts.\n\nACTION:\n0–1s: He slowly turns a radio dial. Static flickers on the CRT monitors.\n1–2s: The ON AIR sign clicks on by itself, casting red light across his face.\n2–3s: He freezes and looks toward the nearest CRT monitor.\n3–4s: The CRT shows a delayed image of him smiling, while the real technician remains terrified and still.\n\nMOTION DETAILS:\nTiny finger tremble, one slow blink, slight CRT flicker, soft cable sway, red light pulse, subtle handheld camera drift.\n\nAUDIO:\nLow electrical hum, radio static, one switch click, faint tape warble. At the final second, a distorted speaker whisper says: “Live.”\n\nMUSIC:\nMinimal vintage synth drone, no drums, low tension.\n\nAVOID:\nNo cuts, no extra characters, no fast action, no monster reveal, no modern computers, no random text, no exaggerated facial expression."
    },
    "class_type": "PrimitiveStringMultiline",
    "_meta": {
      "title": "Prompt"
    }
